{"type":"message","id":"e2747d23","parentId":"c6c5c53a","timestamp":"2026-05-21T03:49:39.535Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The owner is saying that the feedback/edit I posted had a warning. Let me look at my previous edit response. I wrote the file successfully with `write` tool and said \"已撤回，恢复成原来的样子了\" - but that was the write operation, not the edit. The write didn't show any warnings.\n\nActually, wait - looking more carefully, I think the owner might be referring to the edit I attempted earlier that failed with the \"Could not find the exact text\" error (which I showed in the tool result), or they might be referring to the edit from earlier in the conversation when I first modified the script.\n\nLet me re-read the conversation flow:\n1. I first used `edit` to add the `readLogs` function - this succeeded\n2. Then I tried to `edit` to revert but got a \"Could not find the exact text\" error\n3. Then I used `write` to overwrite the whole file\n\nThe owner is probably referring to that failed edit attempt with the warning/error message. Let me check if there's something else they're talking about.\n\nHmm, actually the owner might be looking at the conversation in Feishu where my tool calls/results are shown. They might see the error from the failed edit attempt. Let me just acknowledge and check.\n\nActually wait - the owner said \"你反馈的这个edit有警告\" - \"the edit you reflected has a warning\". They're pointing out that my edit result showed a warning/error. The failed edit attempt that showed:\n\n```\n\"error\": \"Could not find the exact text in C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\...The old text must match exactly including all whitespace and newlines.\"\n```\n\nThat's the warning/error. I should acknowledge it and explain what happened.\n\nActually, maybe I'm overthinking. Let me just apologize and check if there's something to fix.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"抱歉，那个 `edit` 尝试匹配旧文本时没对齐（因为之前写的文件里有