{"type":"message","id":"5550ddf4","parentId":"7466b43d","timestamp":"2026-05-21T03:57:30.260Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually, I don't want to open yet another browser popup - the user might not be at their desk and it'll just confuse things. Let me think about this differently.\n\nThe old `gitlab_cookies.json` was working fine for read operations before I overwrote it by opening the headed browser. The key issue was that `add` got 401, which may have been a different problem (maybe need CSRF token or the session doesn't have enough permission).\n\nWait, actually there might still be a backup from the original session. Let me check if there's any backup of the old cookies.\n\nAlternatively, maybe the initial cookie was valid and the 401 on add was due to the project 2751 not having the right permissions or needing admin-level access for write operations.\n\nLet me check - in the old cookie era, we successfully:\n1. Searched for 胡新雷 ✅\n2. Listed members of 5058 ✅\n3. Listed members of 4710 ✅  \n4. Listed members of 2751 ✅\n5. Failed to add to 2751 ❌ (401)\n\nSo the old cookie was fine for read. The 401 on add was either:\n- Need CSRF token for POST\n- Need admin/owner permission (but 叶枝君 is Owner of 2751)\n- GitLab API requires Personal Access Token for POST operations\n\nGitLab's API v4 requires authentication. For personal accounts, you can either use:\n1. Private token (from user settings)\n2. OAuth tokens\n3. Session cookies\n\nSession cookies from the web UI should work for API calls too, but some operations (especially admin-level) might need CSRF protection.\n\nActually, in GitLab, when using `_gitlab_session` cookie for API calls, you also need to include the CSRF token for POST/PUT/DELETE requests. The CSRF token is `X-CSRF-Token` header obtained from the page's metadata.\n\nLet me check the gitlab API docs - for session-based auth, POST/PUT/DELETE requests need `X-CSRF-Token` header.\n\nLet me take a different approach. I'll open a headed browser, have the user log in, grab both the cookie AND the CSRF token, and then try the add operation.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"明白了，GitLab 写操作（POST/PUT）还需要 CSRF Token。我重新搞一下，让主人先登录，然后同时获取 Cookie + CSRF Token。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_B0Z2aGXIbefDoz6m8kiS0809","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import { chromium } from 'playwright';\nimport fs from 'fs';\n\nconst browser = await chromium.launch({ headless: false });\nconst page = await browser.newPage();\nconsole.log('打开 GitLab...');\nawait page.goto('https://git.devcloud.ztgame.com/', { waitUntil: 'networkidle', timeout: 30000 });\nawait page.waitForTimeout(2000);\nconsole.log('当前页面:', page.url());\n\nconsole.log('请主人登录 GitLab...');\n\n// Wait for successful login (URL changes from sign_in)\ntry {\n  await page.waitForURL(url => !url.toString().includes('sign_in'), { timeout: 300000 });\n  console.log('登录成功! 当前页面:', page.url());\n} catch(e) {\n  console.log('等待超时或出错:', e.message);\n  await browser.close();\n  process.exit(1);\n}\n\n// Wait a bit for page to fully load\nawait page.waitForTimeout(2000);\n\n// Get CSRF token\nconst csrfToken = await page.evaluate(() => {\n  const meta = document.querySelector('meta[name=\"csrf-token\"]');\n  return meta ? meta.getAttribute('content') : null;\n});\nconsole.log('CSRF Token:', csrfToken ? csrfToken.substring(0, 20) + '...' : '❌ 未找到');\n\n// Save cookies\nconst cookies = await page.context().cookies();\nfs.writeFileSync('gitlab_cookies.json', JSON.stringify(cookies, null, 2));\nconsole.log(`Cookie 已保存 (${cookies.length} 个)`);\n\n// Save CSRF token with cookies\nfs.writeFileSync('gitlab_csrf.json', JSON.stringify({ csrfToken, timestamp: new Date().toISOString() }, null, 2));\nconsole.log('CSRF Token 已保存');\n\nconst gs = cookies.find(c => c.name === '_gitlab_session');\nconsole.log('_gitlab_session:', gs ? gs.value.substring(0, 20) + '...' : '⚠️ 未找到');\n\nawait browser.close();\n","path":"