{"type":"message","id":"bc6ff3f1","parentId":"8eb678fc","timestamp":"2026-05-21T04:03:23.177Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, the previous script actually didn't detect the login. Looking at the output again:\n\n\"当前页面: https://git.devcloud.ztgame.com/users/sign_in\"\n\"请主人登录 GitLab...\"\n\"CSRF Token: ⚠️ 未找到\"\n\nThis suggests the browser opened but quickly finished - the `waitForURL` didn't block. Playwright's `waitForURL` with a predicate function might need a different syntax. Or the browser was somehow not seen by the user.\n\nLet me try a fresh approach. The old cookie that worked before was accidentally overwritten. Let me try to see if the old _gitlab_session value can be recovered somehow, or just open a new browser properly.\n\nActually, I realize the problem - when using `waitForURL` with a function, the Playwright API changed. For newer Playwright versions, `waitForURL` accepts:\n- A string (URL pattern)\n- A RegExp\n- A function `(url) => boolean`\n\nBut the function variant was added in Playwright 1.19+. We have 1.60 so it should work. Maybe the issue is that after login, the URL still contains \"sign_in\" in some redirect path, or the function didn't match correctly.\n\nLet me just run the new script.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Cs7fepmOFFkuqCWSUB4j8770","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node scripts\\_gitlab_login.mjs","timeout":600,"workdir":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace","pty":true}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":153,"output":383,"cacheRead":53888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54424,"cost":{"input":0.00002142,"output":0.00010724000000000001,"cacheRead":0.001508864,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001637524}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779336199428,"responseId":"97006c04-06c8-4d23-a29b-ad4601bcb52d"}}
