{"type":"message","id":"f14ab5e9","parentId":"cf89db71","timestamp":"2026-05-21T04:03:39.109Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The login was detected, but it redirected to a Keycloak SSO page (OpenID Connect). The cookies were saved and session is valid, but CSRF token was not found on that page (which makes sense, it's a Keycloak auth page, not a GitLab page).\n\nThe user logged in, cookies saved, but:\n1. We're on a Keycloak auth page now, not a GitLab project page\n2. The CSRF token is missing\n3. The session cookie might not be the fully authenticated GitLab session yet\n\nWe need to wait for the OIDC callback to complete and actually get to a GitLab page. Let me check what URL we're at and try to navigate to a GitLab page.\n\nActually, the cookies have 21 entries now, and the _gitlab_session is valid. But the Keycloak page means the user started the SSO flow but may not have completed it (entered their credentials on the Keycloak page).\n\nWait, actually the URL says `keycloak.devcloud.ztgame.com/auth/realms/giant/protocol/openid-connect/auth` - this is BEFORE the user logs in on the Keycloak page. The flow is: GitLab sign_in → click SSO → redirect to Keycloak for login → after login, Keycloak redirects back to GitLab callback.\n\nSo the browser may still be on the Keycloak login page, waiting for the user to enter their SSO credentials!\n\nLet me check the current session and see if the cookies work for GitLab API.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"登录后进入了 Keycloak SSO 页面，主人可能还需要在 Keycloak 上输一次账号密码才能完成 SSO 登录流程。我先检查一下当前 Cookie 能否用。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ykSYe7q1pc0KyFG7f19x0717","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node scripts/git_permission.mjs list 2751","workdir":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":323,"output":454,"cacheRead":54528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55305,"