{"type":"message","id":"57b5e932","parentId":"375cbe64","timestamp":"2026-05-21T04:05:48.004Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The write operation works now with the fresh CSRF token. Now let me clean up the temp script.\n\nLet me also add a CSRF refresh step to the skill and be more explicit about the token refresh flow.\n\nLet me also think about keeping the CSRF token alive. The token is page-specific and refreshes on each page load. For automation, we should either:\n1. Refresh the CSRF token before each write operation\n2. Or use a personal access token instead of session cookies\n\nActually, a simpler approach would be to make `getWriteHeaders()` automatically fetch a fresh CSRF token if the current one is stale (resulting in 401). Let me update the script to auto-refresh on 401.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"好，CSRF 刷新后写操作恢复正常了。我顺便把这个自动刷新逻辑加到脚本里，省得每次过期了手动搞。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_cDsv2iMJDuk7a93UauPe1967","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node scripts/git_permission.mjs update 2751 胡新雷 reporter","workdir":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":115,"output":266,"cacheRead":71424,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71805,"cost":{"input":0.000016100000000000002,"output":0.00007448,"cacheRead":0.0019998719999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0020904519999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779336344951,"responseId":"57fd8924-d1ea-41bd-bdbc-92838f804b18"}}
