{"type":"message","id":"7db2061b","parentId":"14048ea3","timestamp":"2026-05-21T06:26:45.711Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The `/members/all` endpoint doesn't find 胡新雷 at all, even though he was found in `/members/1836` (direct membership). \n\nIn GitLab, there are two endpoints:\n- `/projects/{id}/members` - only direct members\n- `/projects/{id}/members/all` - direct + inherited members\n\nActually, wait. Looking at the GitLab API docs more carefully:\n- `GET /projects/:id/members` - Gets a list of project members (direct only)\n- `GET /projects/:id/members/all` - Gets a list of project members (including inherited)\n\nThe user with id=1836 is found via `GET /projects/4710/members/1836` (direct lookup) with access_level 20. But not in `GET .../members/all?per_page=200` which should include all members.\n\nThis is unusual. Maybe the members/all endpoint has pagination issues or the user is getting filtered.\n\nLet me look at this more carefully. The `members/all` response returns members sorted by ID or creation. Since 胡新雷 was created at \"2025-12-08\" and has id=1836 (newer than most people), he might be in later pages. Let me check with a more targeted approach.\n\nActually wait - the `members/all` with search parameter also didn't find him before. The search parameter may not search through inherited members properly.\n\nLet me just try a direct API query to GET /projects/4710/members with a search for his user to see if he shows up.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_0tqZm0EDoc1VIAdju3Pi5358","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import fs from 'fs';\n\nconst cookies = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('gitlab_cookies.json', 'utf8'));\nconst cookieStr = cookies.map(c => `${c.name}=${c.value}`).join('; ');\nconst headers = { 'Cookie': cookieStr, 'Accept': 'application/json' };\n\n// Check direct members first\nconst r1 = await fetch('https://git.devcloud.ztgame.com/api/v4/projects/4710/members?per_page=200', { headers });\nconst direct = await r1.json();\nconsole.log('Direct members count:', direct.length);\nconst hx1 = direct.find(m => m.id === 1836);\nif (hx1) console.log('Direct member:', JSON.stringify(hx1, null, 2));\n\n// Check pages of members/all\nconst r2 = await fetch('https://git.devcloud.ztgame.com/api/v4/projects/4710/members/all?per_page=100&page=1', { headers });\nconst all1 = await r2.json();\nconsole.log('\\nmembers/all page 1 count:', all1.length);\nconst hx2 = all1.find(m => m.id === 1836);\nif (hx2) console.log('Found in page 1:', JSON.stringify(hx2, null, 2));\n\nconst r3 = await fetch('https://git.devcloud.ztgame.com/api/v4/projects/4710/members/all?per_page=100&page=2', { headers });\nconst all2 = await r3.json();\nconsole.log('members/all page 2 count:', all2.length);\nconst hx3 = all2.find(m => m.id === 1836);\nif (hx3) console.log('Found in page 2:', JSON.stringify(hx3, null, 2));\n\n// Search specifically\nconst r4 = await fetch('https://git.devcloud.ztgame.com/api/v4/projects/4710/members/all?search=huxinlei', { headers });\nconst search = await r4.json();\nconsole.log('\\nsearch=huxinlei:', JSON.stringify(search, null, 2));\n\n// Check original v-huxinlei\nconst r5 = await fetch('https://git.devcloud.ztgame.com/api/v4/projects/4710/members?search=v-huxinlei', { headers });\nconst search2 = await r5.json();\nconsole.log('\\nmembers search=v-huxinlei:', JSON.stringify(search2, null, 2));\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\_check_member3.mjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":139,"output":939,"cacheRead":86400,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87478,"cost":{"input":0.00001946,"output":0.00026292000000000004,"cacheRead":0.0024192,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00270158}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779344794523,"responseId":"e283f40d-6712-4a49-80a8-8d5b34bd8d5f"}}
