{"type":"message","id":"15b57afc","parentId":"6adc816d","timestamp":"2026-05-21T06:26:57.253Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the issue clearly!\n\nIn `members/all` page 2, 胡新雷 appears with `access_level: 30` (Developer) — not 20 (Reporter)!\n\nThis means the `/members/all` endpoint returns the **effective** access level. Even though we set his direct membership to Reporter (20), his effective access level is still Developer (30). This is because he likely belongs to a group that has Developer+ access to this project. In GitLab, the effective permission is the maximum of direct membership and group membership.\n\nSo the API-level change to Reporter (20) was successful (confirmed by `GET /projects/4710/members/1836` returning access_level 20), but his group membership gives him Developer (30) which overrides it.\n\nWe need to either:\n1. Remove him from the group that gives Developer access, or\n2. Accept that he stays at Developer (since group permissions override direct ones)\n\nBut wait, GitLab has a nuance: when a user is both a direct member and in a group, the effective permission is the **maximum** of the two. So if he's:\n- Direct: Reporter (20)\n- Group: Developer (30)\n- Effective: Developer (30) ← the higher one wins\n\nTo make him Reporter, we'd need to remove him from whatever group gives him Developer access to this project. But that's likely a broader team group that we probably shouldn't touch.\n\nActually, I should report this to the owner. The API says he's Reporter as a direct member, but group membership overrides it to Developer.\n\nLet me also check what group(s) give him access.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"找到原因了！API 查到的实际有效权限是 **Developer(30)**，虽然直接成员已改为 Reporter(20)，但有**组权限**覆盖了它。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_lnoTEcXWScmYft9n1ege0503","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import fs from 'fs';\n\nconst cookies = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('gitlab_cookies.json', 'utf8'));\nconst cookieStr = cookies.map(c => `${c.name}=${c.value}`).join('; ');\nconst headers = { 'Cookie': cookieStr, 'Accept': 'application/json' };\n\n// Check what groups胡新雷 is in\nconst r = await fetch('https://git.devcloud.ztgame.com/api/v4/users/1836/groups?per_page=100', { headers });\nconst groups = await r.json();\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify(groups, null, 2));\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\_check_groups.mjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":8441,"output":588,"cacheRead":87552,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96581,"cost":{"input":0.0011817400000000001,"output":0.00016464000000000002,"cacheRead":0.002451456,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0037978359999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779344808501,"responseId":"760bd887-a5be-461a-ae9e-c87ae87dff70"}}
