{"type":"message","id":"db7dc556","parentId":"08c42703","timestamp":"2026-05-21T07:16:04.672Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The owner is saying that when skills are updated, other sessions/agents don't have the latest version. He wants skills to automatically sync/update across sessions whenever they're changed.\n\nThis is a deeper architectural question about OpenClaw's skill system. Let me think about this:\n\n1. Skills are stored at `~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`\n2. When I read a skill file at the start of a session, I get whatever is on disk\n3. But different sessions (sub-agents, forked sessions) might have cached/older versions\n\nThe key issue: if I update a skill file (like SKILL.md or a script it references), the changes are on disk immediately, but other running sessions won't know about it until they re-read the skill.\n\nThis is actually how it works - the skill files are read from disk each time a session starts. So if skills are updated, new sessions will pick them up automatically. But existing running sessions won't.\n\nSome ideas:\n1. **Memory mapping**: When updating a skill, write a note to MEMORY.md so new sessions can check\n2. **Version tracking**: Each skill has a version number, and sessions check if they have the latest\n3. **Sessions.yaml/config actuality**: There might not be a native mechanism\n\nActually, thinking more carefully - the owner is talking about the skills in the `~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/` directory. These are READ by the agent when triggered. If I update a SKILL.md file, the next time any session reads it, it'll get the new content. So new sessions will always see the latest.\n\nBut wait - the issue is more about the scripts and reference files. When I update `git_permission.mjs`, that's at `workspace/scripts/git_permission.mjs`. All sessions share the same workspace. Any process running `node scripts/git_permission.mjs` will pick up the latest file.\n\nSo I think the issue might be:\n1. The SKILL.md is cached in session memory once read - but the actual trigger logic re-reads it\n2. Or the owner wants a way to \"propagate\" skill changes to all existing sessions\n\nActually, I think the owner's concern is simpler than I'm making it. They want that whenever I update a skill (SKILL.md or associated scripts), the new version is available everywhere immediately. Since everything is file-based, this should already be the case.\n\nBut there might be a subtlety: when I \"update\" a skill by editing SKILL.md, new sessions reading the file at startup will see the changes. But what about the current session? The SKILL.md is already loaded.\n\nActually, the `/skills` API or whatever loads the skill - it reads from disk each time the skill is triggered. So any session can always get the latest.\n\nHmm, but the owner has experience with this not working, saying \"经常有设置别的session没有同步到\". So there might be a caching issue.\n\nLet me think about what I can do:\n\n1. When I modify a skill file, I can also update MEMORY.md with a \"skill version\" timestamp\n2. When a new task comes in, before reading the SKILL.md, check if there's a newer version in MEMORY.md\n\nActually, the simplest and most robust approach: create a `workspace/scripts/sync_skills.mjs` script that copies skill config into the workspace (or vice versa), and add it to the skill update flow. But that's over-engineering.\n\nMore practically: the issue might be that I'm editing SKILL.md in the skill directory, but the session has already read it. The solution would be:\n1. Write the skill changes to the workspace directory as reference\n2. Or use MEMORY.md as a \"what changed\" log that new sessions can check\n\nActually, the simplest solution that addresses the owner's concern: whenever I update a skill (edit SKILL.md or scripts), I should ALSO update MEMORY.md with a note about what changed and when. This way, any session that needs the skill can check MEMORY.md for the latest version info.\n\nWait, but actually the real issue might be simpler. Let me re-read the owner's message:\n\n\"经常有设置别的session没有同步到，每次更新技能能不能自动同步\"\n\nTranslation: \"Settings often don't sync to other sessions. Can you auto-sync when updating skills?\"\n\nThe owner wants that when I update a skill, all other sessions automatically get the changes. Since skills are file-based, new sessions DO get changes. The problem might be with:\n1. Sessions that have already read the skill and cached the info in their context\n2. Configuration in the SKILL.md that other agents reference\n\nActually, I think the real concern is about the SKILL.md itself. When I edit a SKILL.md (like gitlab-permission/SKILL.md), other sessions that need that skill will re-read it from disk fresh. So actually it SHOULD work.\n\nUnless... the issue is that when I say \"update skill in memory\" or \"save skill data to TOOLS.md/MEMORY.md\", the other sessions check MEMORY.md but not the SKILL.md directly?\n\nLet me just address this practically:\n\nThe best approach: maintain a \"skills manifest\" that tracks version/update time, and whenever a task needs a skill, check if the manifest says there's a newer version than what's currently loaded.\n\nBut that's complex. Let me think simpler:\n\n**Simple solution:** Create a `memory/skills-manifest.json` that tracks the last update time of each skill. When any session needs a skill, first check this manifest for the latest update timestamp. If newer than what the session knows about, re-read the SKILL.md from disk.\n\nOr even simpler: just acknowledge the issue and suggest that skills ARE file-based and automatically picked up by new sessions, but for the current session, I can implement a \"skill version check\" pattern.\n\nLet me just respond practically:\n\n1. Skills ARE on disk and new sessions always read them fresh\n2. The issue might be that I also need to update TOOLS.md or MEMORY.md when I update a skill\n3. I can create a simple system: when updating a skill, write version info to `memory/skills-manifest.json`, and before reading any skill, check this manifest\n\nActually, you know what, let me just propose a practical solution and ask the owner if that's what they want.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"这个确实是问题。目前每个 session 收到任务时我会**重新读 SKILL.md**（文件在磁盘上，新 session 读到的就是最新的），但问题是：\n\n1. **同一个 session 里**我只读一次 skill，中途改技能不会重新读\n2. **子 session**（sub-agent）启动时读的版本，和主 session 可能不同\n\n我想搞个**技能版本追踪**方案——"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_81opOkoYGxhjIII5JkuL4483","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"{\n  \"gitlab-permission\": {\n    \"version\": 2,\n    \"updatedAt\": \"2026-05-21T14:30:00.000Z\",\n    \"description\": \"GitLab 权限管理，CSRF Token + writeWithRetry + 组权限覆盖规则\"\n  },\n  \"tapd-bug-create\": {\n    \"version\": 1,\n    \"updatedAt\": \"2026-05-18T00:00:00.000Z\",\n    \"description\": \"TAPD 自动提单\"\n  },\n  \"tapd-vsmode-story\": {\n    \"version\": 1,\n    \"updatedAt\": \"2026-05-20T00:00:00.000Z\",\n    \"description\": \"1V1 VSMODE 需求单\"\n  }\n}\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\skills-manifest.json"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":11653,"output":1698,"cacheRead":98304,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111655,"cost":{"input":0.0016314200000000002,"output":0.00047544000000000004,"cacheRead":0.002752512,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004859372000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779347735638,"responseId":"71365da1-5883-4f5b-b687-7310442d3e7c"}}
