{"type":"message","id":"4cfd4877","parentId":"e071d100","timestamp":"2026-05-21T07:16:33.419Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_LujllCJqPspnLaLPjBQR8889","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\MEMORY.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  70 - **Cookie 文件：** `workspace/devops_cookies.json`\n  71 - **HEARTBEAT 集成：** `HEARTBEAT.md` 已配置，每天自动检查两个保活状态\n  72 - **退出码：** 0=成功续期 / 1=登录失效需重新登录 / 2=脚本错误\n  73 \n+ 74 ## 技能版本管理（2026-05-21）\n+ 75 \n+ 76 - **清单文件：** `memory/skills-manifest.json`\n+ 77 - **机制：** 每次更新技能（SKILL.md/脚本/TOOLS.md）时，同步 bump 清单中的版本号\n+ 78 - **使用方式：** 每次触发技能前检查清单版本，比记忆中的新则重新从磁盘读取 SKILL.md\n+ 79 - 当前技能版本：gitlab-permission=v2, tapd-bug-create=v1, tapd-vsmode-story=v1\n+ 80 \n  74 ## GitLab 登录保活（2026-05-21）\n  75 \n  76 - **保活脚本：** `workspace/scripts/gitlab_keepalive.mjs`\n  77 - **原理：** 每天 headless 访问一次 GitLab 首页，服务器 session 会自动续期\n     ...","firstChangedLine":74},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779347793419}}
{"type":"message","id":"15bf7171","parentId":"4cfd4877","timestamp":"2026-05-21T07:16:41.562Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I also need to update AGENTS.md to tell future sessions to check the skills manifest before using a skill. Let me add that instruction.\n\nActually, looking at the startup flow more carefully:\n\nWhen OpenClaw starts a session, it reads:\n1. AGENTS.md - workspace rules\n2. SOUL.md - personality\n3. MEMORY.md - curated memory\n4. TOOLS.md - local notes\n5. HEARTBEAT.md - periodic tasks\n\nThen throughout the session, when I need a skill:\n1. I check `<available_skills>` which lists skills\n2. I read the SKILL.md at the listed location\n3. I execute\n\nThe problem is: between when I read SKILL.md and when I need to act on it, the skill might have been updated by another session/agent. But since I read SKILL.md right when I need it (not cached in session startup), this should be fine.\n\nThe only scenario where it breaks is:\n1. Read SKILL.md → get version 1\n2. Another session updates SKILL.md to version 2\n3. My session continues to use version 1 (stale in my context)\n\nBut this is an inherent limitation of conversation-based agents. I can't really \"un-read\" something from my context.\n\nThe practical solution: tell future sessions to check the manifest before reading. That way they always know the latest version.\n\nLet me add this to AGENTS.md instead of trying to add it to my startup context which is already loaded.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_oowQwHhL6UZJ2GCstKgI5384","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{}]}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":166,"output":555,"cacheRead":113152,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":113873,"cost":{"input":0.00002324,"output":0.0001554,"cacheRead":0.003168256,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003346896}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779347793421,"responseId":"69edea4a-fc25-4b68-8f8d-1c2b7985e47f"}}
